      {
        "type": "h2",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Integration Steps for Production Environments"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Setting up Nanonets OCR S ocr involves obtaining API credentials and configuring your client for robust communication. Start by signing up at the "
          },
          {
            "type": "a",
            "url": "https://nanonets.com/api",
            "title": null,
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Nanonets API portal"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " to generate an API key. This key must be included in all requests via the "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Authorization",
            "code": true
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " header. For production, use environment variables to store the key securely—never hard-code it in your source."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "ol",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "li",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "lic",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Install the SDK or use HTTP clients",
                    "bold": true
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": ": While Nanonets provides official SDKs for Python and JavaScript, you can also use direct HTTP calls. For Python, install via pip: "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "pip install nanonets-ocr",
                    "code": true
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "li",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "lic",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Configure timeouts and retries",
                    "bold": true
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": ": Network issues can occur; set a timeout of 30 seconds and implement exponential backoff for retries on 5xx errors."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "li",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "lic",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Test with a sample image",
                    "bold": true
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": ": Validate your setup by sending a simple request before integrating into your workflow."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "blockquote",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Note:",
            "bold": true
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " The API enforces rate limits of 100 requests per minute on the standard tier. Exceeding this returns a "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "429 Too Many Requests",
            "code": true
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " error. Plan your throughput accordingly or contact support for higher limits."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Here's a basic bash command to test connectivity using curl:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "code_block",
        "lang": "bash",
        "value": "curl -X POST https://api.nanonets.com/v2/ocr/model/nanonets-ocr-s \\\n  -H \"Authorization: Basic YOUR_API_KEY\" \\\n  -F \"file=@sample_invoice.png\" \\\n  -F \"format=json\"",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "code_line",
